{"id": "4adfa78c-2400-45d4-9da2-78bc8cf57a6e", "task_id": "6a216a7b-bc78-4082-a6bf-dd24bb9a3b39", "path": "templates/index.html", "artifact_type": "file", "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Cyberpunk Login // System Access</title>\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Orbitron:wght@400;700&family=Share+Tech+Mono&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <style>\n        :root {\n            --dark-bg: #1a0a20; /* Deep dark purple/black */\n            --neon-blue: #00eaff;\n            --neon-magenta: #ee00ff;\n            --neon-green: #00ff99;\n            --text-color: #e0e0e0;\n            --border-glow: 0 0 8px var(--neon-blue), 0 0 16px var(--neon-magenta);\n            --text-glow-blue: 0 0 5px var(--neon-blue), 0 0 10px var(--neon-blue);\n            --text-glow-magenta: 0 0 5px var(--neon-magenta), 0 0 10px var(--neon-magenta);\n            --text-glow-green: 0 0 5px var(--neon-green), 0 0 10px var(--neon-green);\n            --error-red: #ff3366;\n        }\n\n        body {\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;\n            background: linear-gradient(45deg, #0f001f, #05000f); /* Dark gradient background */\n            color: var(--text-color);\n            display: flex;\n            justify-content: center;\n            align-items: center;\n            min-height: 100vh;\n            overflow: hidden; /* Hide potential overflow from glitch effects */\n            position: relative;\n        }\n\n        /* Glitch effect on body background (optional, for more immersion) */\n        body::before {\n            content: '';\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n            background: repeating-linear-gradient(\n                0deg,\n                rgba(0, 234, 255, 0.05) 0px,\n                rgba(0, 234, 255, 0.05) 1px,\n                transparent 1px,\n                transparent 3px\n            );\n            animation: background-scan 10s linear infinite;\n            pointer-events: none;\n            opacity: 0.1;\n            z-index: 0;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes background-scan {\n            0% { background-position: 0 0; }\n            100% { background-position: 0 100%; }\n        }\n\n        .login-container {\n            background-color: var(--dark-bg);\n            padding: 40px;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            box-shadow: var(--border-glow);\n            text-align: center;\n            width: 90%;\n            max-width: 400px;\n            position: relative;\n            z-index: 1; /* Ensure container is above background effects */\n            border: 1px solid var(--neon-blue); /* Subtle border */\n            animation: container-pulse 5s infinite alternate; /* Pulsing effect for the container */\n        }\n\n        @keyframes container-pulse {\n            0% { transform: scale(1); box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--neon-blue), 0 0 20px var(--neon-magenta); }\n            100% { transform: scale(1.01); box-shadow: 0 0 15px var(--neon-blue), 0 0 30px var(--neon-magenta); }\n        }\n\n        .login-glitch-effect {\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n            overflow: hidden;\n            pointer-events: none;\n            opacity: 0.05; /* Subtle glitch background */\n            background: repeating-linear-gradient(\n                45deg,\n                rgba(238, 0, 255, 0.1) 0px,\n                rgba(238, 0, 255, 0.1) 1px,\n                transparent 1px,\n                transparent 5px\n            ), repeating-linear-gradient(\n                135deg,\n                rgba(0, 234, 255, 0.1) 0px,\n                rgba(0, 234, 255, 0.1) 1px,\n                transparent 1px,\n                transparent 5px\n            );\n            animation: glitch-bg 10s infinite linear;\n            z-index: -1; /* Behind content */\n        }\n\n        @keyframes glitch-bg {\n            0% { background-position: 0 0; }\n            100% { background-position: 100% 100%; }\n        }\n\n        .main-title {\n            font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;\n            color: var(--neon-blue);\n            font-size: 2.5em;\n            text-shadow: var(--text-glow-blue);\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\n            letter-spacing: 2px;\n            animation: text-flicker 3s infinite alternate;\n        }\n\n        .sub-title {\n            font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;\n            color: var(--neon-magenta);\n            font-size: 1.2em;\n            text-shadow: var(--text-glow-magenta);\n            margin-top: 0;\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\n            animation: text-flicker 4s infinite reverse;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes text-flicker {\n            0%, 19%, 21%, 23%, 25%, 54%, 56%, 100% {\n                text-shadow: var(--text-glow-blue); /* Primary glow */\n                opacity: 1;\n            }\n            20%, 24%, 55% {\n                text-shadow: none;\n                opacity: 0.8;\n            }\n            22% {\n                text-shadow: var(--text-glow-magenta); /* Brief flicker to another color */\n                opacity: 0.9;\n            }\n        }\n\n        .error-message {\n            color: var(--error-red); /* Red for errors */\n            font-size: 0.9em;\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--error-red), 0 0 10px var(--error-red);\n            animation: error-glow 1.5s infinite alternate;\n            padding: 5px;\n            border-radius: 3px;\n            border: 1px solid var(--error-red);\n            background-color: rgba(255, 51, 102, 0.1);\n        }\n\n        @keyframes error-glow {\n            0% { text-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--error-red); opacity: 1; }\n            100% { text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--error-red), 0 0 20px var(--error-red); opacity: 0.8; }\n        }\n\n        .form-group {\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n            text-align: left;\n            position: relative;\n        }\n\n        label {\n            display: block;\n            margin-bottom: 8px;\n            color: var(--neon-green);\n            text-shadow: var(--text-glow-green);\n            font-size: 0.9em;\n            letter-spacing: 0.5px;\n        }\n\n        input[type=\"text\"],\n        input[type=\"password\"] {\n            width: calc(100% - 20px); /* Account for padding */\n            padding: 10px;\n            background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);\n            border: 1px solid rgba(0, 234, 255, 0.3);\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            color: var(--text-color);\n            font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;\n            font-size: 1em;\n            outline: none;\n            transition: border-color 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;\n        }\n\n        input[type=\"text\"]:focus,\n        input[type=\"password\"]:focus {\n            border-color: var(--neon-blue);\n            box-shadow: var(--border-glow);\n        }\n\n        .login-button {\n            width: 100%;\n            padding: 12px;\n            background: linear-gradient(45deg, var(--neon-blue), var(--neon-magenta));\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            color: #fff;\n            font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;\n            font-size: 1.1em;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--neon-blue), 0 0 20px var(--neon-magenta);\n            transition: background 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease, transform 0.1s ease;\n            position: relative;\n            overflow: hidden;\n        }\n\n        .login-button:hover {\n            background: linear-gradient(45deg, var(--neon-magenta), var(--neon-blue));\n            box-shadow: 0 0 15px var(--neon-magenta), 0 0 25px var(--neon-blue);\n            transform: translateY(-2px);\n        }\n\n        .login-button:active {\n            transform: translateY(0);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--neon-blue), 0 0 10px var(--neon-magenta);\n        }\n\n        /* Glitch effect for button on hover/active */\n        .login-button::before {\n            content: '>> ACCESSING <<';\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n            display: flex;\n            justify-content: center;\n            align-items: center;\n            background: linear-gradient(45deg, var(--neon-blue), var(--neon-magenta));\n            color: #fff;\n            opacity: 0;\n            transition: opacity 0.3s ease;\n            text-shadow: var(--text-glow-blue);\n            animation: none;\n        }\n\n        .login-button:hover::before {\n            opacity: 1;\n            animation: button-glitch 0.5s linear infinite alternate;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes button-glitch {\n            0% {\n                text-shadow: var(--text-glow-blue);\n                transform: translate(0);\n            }\n            33% {\n                text-shadow: var(--text-glow-magenta);\n                transform: translate(-2px, 2px);\n            }\n            66% {\n                text-shadow: var(--text-glow-green);\n                transform: translate(2px, -2px);\n            }\n            100% {\n                text-shadow: var(--text-glow-blue);\n                transform: translate(0);\n            }\n        }\n\n        .login-button.button-submitting {\n            background: #555; /* Dimmed */\n            cursor: wait;\n            pointer-events: none; /* Prevent double clicks */\n            box-shadow: 0 0 5px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\n            transform: translateY(0);\n        }\n        .login-button.button-submitting::before {\n            content: '>>> CONNECTING <<<';\n            opacity: 1;\n            animation: none; /* Disable hover glitch */\n            background: linear-gradient(45deg, #70aeff, #ff70ee); /* Submitting glow */\n            text-shadow: 0 0 5px #fff;\n        }\n\n        .links {\n            margin-top: 30px;\n            display: flex;\n            justify-content: space-between;\n            font-size: 0.85em;\n        }\n\n        .links a {\n            color: var(--neon-green);\n            text-decoration: none;\n            text-shadow: var(--text-glow-green);\n            transition: color 0.3s ease, text-shadow 0.3s ease;\n        }\n\n        .links a:hover {\n            color: #fff;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--neon-green), 0 0 20px var(--neon-green), 0 0 30px var(--neon-green);\n        }\n\n        /* Responsive adjustments */\n        @media (max-width: 500px) {\n            .login-container {\n                padding: 25px;\n                width: 85%;\n            }\n\n            .main-title {\n                font-size: 2em;\n            }\n\n            .sub-title {\n                font-size: 1em;\n                margin-bottom: 20px;\n            }\n\n            .links {\n                flex-direction: column;\n                gap: 10px;\n            }\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"login-container\">\n        <div class=\"login-glitch-effect\"></div>\n        <h1 class=\"main-title\">NEO-LOGIN</h1>\n        <h2 class=\"sub-title\">SYSTEM ACCESS REQUIRED</h2>\n\n        {% if error_message %}\n        <div class=\"error-message\" id=\"backend-error\">{{ error_message }}</div>\n        {% endif %}\n\n        <div class=\"error-message\" id=\"client-error\" style=\"display: none;\"></div>\n\n        <form action=\"/login\" method=\"POST\" id=\"loginForm\">\n            <div class=\"form-group\">\n                <label for=\"username\">USERNAME:</label>\n                <input type=\"text\" id=\"username\" name=\"username\" placeholder=\"enter your handle\" required autocomplete=\"off\">\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"form-group\">\n                <label for=\"password\">PASSWORD:</label>\n                <input type=\"password\" id=\"password\" name=\"password\" placeholder=\"secure access code\" required autocomplete=\"off\">\n            </div>\n            <button type=\"submit\" class=\"login-button\">ACCESS SYSTEM</button>\n        </form>\n\n        <div class=\"links\">\n            <a href=\"#\" class=\"neon-green-glow\">FORGOT PASSWORD?</a>\n            <a href=\"#\" class=\"neon-green-glow\">CREATE ACCOUNT</a>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n            const loginForm = document.getElementById('loginForm');\n            const usernameInput = document.getElementById('username');\n            const passwordInput = document.getElementById('password');\n            const clientErrorMessageDiv = document.getElementById('client-error');\n            const backendErrorMessageDiv = document.getElementById('backend-error'); // Reference for clearing backend errors\n            const loginButton = document.querySelector('.login-button');\n\n            const clearErrors = () => {\n                clientErrorMessageDiv.style.display = 'none';\n                clientErrorMessageDiv.textContent = '';\n                if (backendErrorMessageDiv) {\n                    backendErrorMessageDiv.style.display = 'none';\n                    backendErrorMessageDiv.textContent = '';\n                }\n            };\n\n            const displayClientError = (message) => {\n                clientErrorMessageDiv.textContent = message;\n                clientErrorMessageDiv.style.display = 'block';\n                // Add a temporary class for a pulse animation if desired, otherwise rely on static error-message style\n                clientErrorMessageDiv.classList.add('pulse-error');\n                setTimeout(() => {\n                    clientErrorMessageDiv.classList.remove('pulse-error');\n                }, 1500); // Remove after a short period\n            };\n\n            // Clear errors when user starts typing\n            usernameInput.addEventListener('input', clearErrors);\n            passwordInput.addEventListener('input', clearErrors);\n\n            loginForm.addEventListener('submit', (event) => {\n                // IMPORTANT: Do NOT call event.preventDefault() here.\n                // The form MUST submit to the backend for server-side validation.\n\n                clearErrors(); // Clear any previous client or backend errors\n\n                // Perform client-side validation for immediate feedback\n                if (usernameInput.value.trim() === '') {\n                    displayClientError('Username cannot be empty.');\n                } else if (passwordInput.value.trim() === '') {\n                    displayClientError('Password cannot be empty.');\n                } else if (usernameInput.value.trim().length < 3) {\n                    displayClientError('Username must be at least 3 characters.');\n                } else if (passwordInput.value.trim().length < 6) {\n                    displayClientError('Password must be at least 6 characters.');\n                }\n\n                // Visual feedback for button submission\n                loginButton.classList.add('button-submitting');\n                // Remove after a short period, assuming a quick submit or server response will reload/redirect\n                setTimeout(() => {\n                    loginButton.classList.remove('button-submitting');\n                }, 2000); \n            });\n\n            // If a backend error message is present on page load, ensure it's visible.\n            if (backendErrorMessageDiv && backendErrorMessageDiv.textContent.trim() !== '') {\n                backendErrorMessageDiv.style.display = 'block';\n            }\n        });\n\n        // Dynamically add CSS for client error pulse (reusing existing error-glow keyframes)\n        const style = document.createElement('style');\n        style.textContent = `\n            .pulse-error {\n                animation: error-glow 0.5s linear 3 alternate; /* Quick pulse for client-side errors */\n            }\n        `;\n        document.head.appendChild(style);\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n", "patches": [], "metadata": {"language": "html", "framework": "static_html", "explanation": "This `index.html` file creates a cyberpunk-themed login page. It includes:\n\n1.  **HTML5 Structure**: Standard `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<head>`, and `<body>` tags with meta information for responsiveness and character set. It links to Google Fonts ('Orbitron' for titles, 'Share Tech Mono' for body text).\n2.  **Embedded CSS**: Extensive CSS styling is directly embedded within a `<style>` tag in the `<head>` section. This CSS provides:\n    *   A dark, gradient background with subtle scanning lines.\n    *   A central login container with a dark background, rounded borders, and pulsing neon `box-shadow`s (blue and magenta).\n    *   `h1` and `h2` titles (\"NEO-LOGIN\", \"SYSTEM ACCESS REQUIRED\") with electric blue and magenta neon `text-shadow`s and `text-flicker` animations.\n    *   Input fields (`username`, `password`) styled with dark backgrounds, neon borders on focus, and futuristic fonts.\n    *   A prominent login button with a gradient background, bold text, neon `box-shadow`s, and a `button-glitch` effect on hover.\n    *   'Forgot Password?' and 'Create Account' links styled with neon green color and glow effects.\n    *   A dedicated style for error messages (red neon glow) that pulses.\n    *   Responsive design considerations via a media query for smaller screens.\n3.  **Jinja2 Integration**: The page uses Jinja2 templating syntax (`{% if error_message %}`, `{{ error_message }}`) to conditionally display an error message passed from the FastAPI backend (e.g., after a failed login attempt).\n4.  **Login Form**: A standard HTML `<form action=\"/login\" method=\"POST\" id=\"loginForm\">` is provided for username and password submission. **Crucially, client-side JavaScript does NOT use `event.preventDefault()`**; the form is configured to submit directly to the `/login` endpoint as a POST request, ensuring the backend handles the primary validation and authentication.\n5.  **Embedded Vanilla JavaScript**: Basic client-side JavaScript is included within a `<script>` tag at the end of the `<body>`. It performs the following:\n    *   **Clear Errors on Input**: When a user types into an input field, any visible client-side or backend-provided error messages are cleared.\n    *   **Non-blocking Client-side Validation**: On form submission, it checks if username and password fields are empty or too short. If validation fails, it displays a message in a dedicated `client-error` div. However, it explicitly **does not prevent the form from submitting**, allowing the backend to perform its critical validation.\n    *   **Visual Feedback**: Adds a temporary `button-submitting` class to the login button on submission for visual feedback.\n    *   Ensures that any backend-provided `error_message` is properly displayed on page load.\n\nThe overall design aims for a high-quality, immersive cyberpunk aesthetic while adhering strictly to the requirement of not blocking form submission with JavaScript.", "dependencies": []}, "created_at": "2026-06-17 16:11:33.473100"}